usage: myhelp tmux

prefix = Ctrl+B  (press before every command below)

sessions:
   tmux                      Start new session
   tmux new -s name          Start named session
   tmux ls                   List sessions
   tmux a -t name            Attach to session
   prefix  $                 Rename current session
   prefix  s                 Switch / list sessions
   prefix  d                 Detach (leave session running)

windows (tabs):
   prefix  c                 New window
   prefix  ,                 Rename window
   prefix  n                 Next window
   prefix  p                 Previous window
   prefix  1-9               Jump to window by number
   prefix  &                 Kill window

panes (splits):
   prefix  v                 Split vertically (side by side)
   prefix  h                 Split horizontally (top/bottom)
   prefix  arrow keys        Navigate panes
   prefix  H/J/K/L           Resize pane (hold prefix + repeat)
   prefix  Ctrl+arrows       Resize pane (alternative)
   prefix  z                 Zoom pane (fullscreen toggle)
   prefix  x                 Kill pane

copy mode:
   prefix  [                 Enter copy mode
   v                         Start selection
   y                         Copy selection and exit
   q  or  Escape             Exit copy mode

other:
   prefix  r                 Reload config
   prefix  ?                 Show this cheatsheet inside tmux
